Nigerian music legend and reggae king Majekodunmi Fasheke, popularly known as Majek Fashek, has been announced dead. His longtime manager, Umenka Uzoma made the announcement on Tuesday, June 2, 2022. According to him, “Today been having pressure calls, well it is true that the African No 1 Legendary ICON has gone to be with the LORD his Maker, he said. “Let celebrate him, his achievements, and his family, whatever decisions made by his immediate family will be notified.” Recall that Fashek had been suffering from an illness for years. He was one of the biggest music exports from this part of the world in the late 1980s and the early 1990s. 